name: CUANDO NACI. AHORA MISMO. CUANDO MORI.
description: English is my first language, but I quasi-competently speak Spanish as well and learning others here and there. I find each written language a pool of inspiration; each unique and special from the next. In CUANDO NACI. (When I was born.) AHORA MISMO. (Now I'm alive now or right now.) CUANO MORI. (When I died.), we're dealing with different tenses of time. First the far past, then present, and then strangely future past tense, as if I'm writing it from beyond the grave. Andy Warhol famously said, "The idea is not to live forever, it is to create something that will.” Whether this will last beyond my years remains up to you, the reader, to decide.
